Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # 1. Install system packages
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        git \
        python3 \
        python3-pip
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # 2. Install Python tooling (pytest for test harness)
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # 3. Create project directory structure
    PROJECT_DIR="/home/user/projects/acme-service"
    mkdir -p "${PROJECT_DIR}"

    # 4. Populate VERSION file
    cat > "${PROJECT_DIR}/VERSION" <<'EOF'
2.4.1
EOF

    # 5. Populate CHANGELOG.md with required initial content
    cat > "${PROJECT_DIR}/CHANGELOG.md" <<'EOF'
# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [2.4.1] - 2023-06-15
- Fixed authentication middleware race condition (#342)

## [2.4.0] - 2023-05-28
- Added OAuth2 support (#315)
EOF

    # 6. Initialise Git repository with a single commit on branch "main"
    cd "${PROJECT_DIR}"
    git init -b main
    git config user.email "builder@example.com"
    git config user.name  "Builder"
    git add VERSION CHANGELOG.md
    git commit -m "Initial commit"

    # 7. Ensure write permissions for the runtime (non-root) user
    chmod -R a+rwX /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author "Apptainer build script for ACME service patch-release exercise"

%help
    Container pre-configured for the “patch-release” exercise.
    Includes:
      • Git repository at /home/user/projects/acme-service (version 2.4.1)
      • Python3 + pytest
      • All files world-writable so an unprivileged user can complete the task.